Here is the Python version of your function:

```python
def clean_column(col):
    return col.strip().lower().replace(" ", "_").replace("-", "_")
```
This function works by first stripping any leading or trailing whitespace using `strip()`. It then converts all characters to lowercase with `lower()`, replaces spaces with underscores, and hyphens with underscores, using `replace()` twice. 

If you want the same functionality in Julia, here's how you can do it:

```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return lowercase(strip(col)).replace(" ", "_").replace("-", "_")
end
```
This function uses `lowercase` to convert all characters to lower case, `strip` to remove leading and trailing whitespace, and `replace` to replace spaces and hyphens with underscores.
